MPs have vowed to resist plans to reduce the National Government Constituencies Development Fund (NG-CDF). Speaking on Monday in separate functions, the leaders said Kenyans were already feeling the heat of heavy taxation. ALSO READ:

MPs run out of options in bid to stop Uhuru taxes “Those advising the President should stop misleading him. Reducing NG-CDF is not an option. The only feasible projects in constituencies are those funded by the fund,” said Bomachoge Chache MP Alfa Miruka. “We will reject any proposal to scale down funding to the constituency and woman representative kitties," said Kisii Woman Rep Janet Ong'era.